<subSubSection id="B59399A3B012FFE9A19AFA29FD6E1CD8" pageId="17" pageNumber="385" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="FD36CA28B012FFE9A19AFA29FD6E1CD8" blockId="17.[125,772,1397,2100]" pageId="17" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis id="CFFD163AB012FFE9A19AFA29FE8D1CA6" box="[155,269,1431,1455]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="385">Etymology</emphasis>
:Acombination of 
<collectingCountry id="859E8AB8B012FFE9A0D9FA27FD991CA6" box="[472,537,1433,1455]" name="Iran" pageId="17" pageNumber="385">Persia</collectingCountry>
and 
<emphasis id="CFFD163AB012FFE9A34DFA29FDFA1CA6" box="[588,634,1431,1455]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="385">lena</emphasis>
referring to similarity with the genus 
<taxonomicName id="3A89B1ABB012FFE9A08DFA07FE631CD8" authorityName=": Lehtinen" authorityYear="1967" box="[396,483,1465,1489]" class="Arachnida" family="Agelenidae" genus="Agelena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="17" pageNumber="385" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="CFFD163AB012FFE9A08DFA07FE631CD8" box="[396,483,1465,1489]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="385">Agelena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The gender is feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B59399A3B012FFE9A19AFA62FDB21F51" pageId="17" pageNumber="385" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="FD36CA28B012FFE9A19AFA62FDB21F51" blockId="17.[125,772,1397,2100]" pageId="17" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis id="CFFD163AB012FFE9A19AFA62FE871CFA" box="[155,263,1500,1523]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="385">Diagnosis</emphasis>
: The new genus differs from all other Old World Agelenini by lacking an epigynal fovea (atrium) (
<taxonomicName id="3A89B1ABB012FFE9A3E6FA40FF501F3F" pageId="17" pageNumber="385" rank="variety" variety="present">
<emphasis id="CFFD163AB012FFE9A3E6FA40FD771F1C" box="[743,759,1534,1557]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="385">v.</emphasis>
present
</taxonomicName>
) and the slit-like copulatory openings (
<taxonomicName id="3A89B1ABB012FFE9A36FF99EFD781F3F" box="[622,760,1568,1591]" pageId="17" pageNumber="385" rank="variety" variety="copulatory">
<emphasis id="CFFD163AB012FFE9A36FF99EFDFE1F3E" box="[622,638,1568,1591]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="385">v.</emphasis>
copulatory
</taxonomicName>
openings located in fovea) (
<figureCitation id="65B2D6ADB012FFE9A0A3F9FDFE7D1F51" box="[418,509,1603,1625]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="15.[125,156,1431,1450]" captionTargetBox="[126,1461,151,1406]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[126,1461,151,1406]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig. 14: Epigynes. A Gorbiscape gorbachevi sp. n., intact, ventral view; B same, macerated, dorsal view; C, D same, posterior views; E, F Asiascape parthica sp. n., intact, ventral views; G same, macerated, dorsal view; H same, posterior view; I Persilena sengleti sp. n., posterior view; D same, intact, ventral view; K same, antero-ventral view; L same, dorsal view. Scale bars = 0.2 mm. Abbreviation: Cd = copulatory duct." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3925245" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3925245/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="385">Figs. 14</figureCitation>
I–L).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B59399A3B012FFE9A19AF9DAFE6C1F72" box="[155,492,1636,1659]" pageId="17" pageNumber="385" type="description">
